Renton.East Renton Highlands, Washington:
East Renton Highlands is a census-designated place (CDP) in King County, Washington, United States, located between Issaquah and Renton. The population was 11,140 at the 2010 census.
East Renton Highlands is part of the potential annexation area (PAA)[1] of Renton, but in February 2007 voters defeated a 1,475-acre (5.97 km2) annexation proposal 3 to 1.
